Young striker Jack Harper wants to follow in Gareth Bale's footsteps at Real Madrid

'It's an inspiration seeing them because that's obviously what I want to be in a year or two. There's nothing better than walking in and seeing Gareth Bale and Cristiano Ronaldo,' said Harper in an SFA interview ahead of Scotland Under 19s' European Championship qualifiers.

'When Gareth signed, I said to him "look, if you need any help or anyone to talk to I'm here".'

Bale did make a slow start in Spain despite a goal in his first game as injuries hampered his early progress, but 22 goals and a cup double capped a superb debut season. Now Harper hopes to follow in his footsteps.

