'I've seen him a couple of times and hopefully in a year or two we'll be team-mates,' said the 18-year-old.

Harper stood out for the Madrid kids against Basle in the UEFA Youth League last month, scoring once, hitting the bar, smacking the post and forcing the keeper into a couple of smart saves in a 2-0 victory.

He is now on international duty with the young Scots facing Finland on Tuesday, Lithuania on Thursday and Norway on October 12.

